WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.802
Infection Control

00:00:01.802 --> 00:00:03.252
Protocols:

00:00:03.252 --> 00:00:05.742
Sterilization and Disinfection:

00:00:05.742 --> 00:00:12.761
All instruments must be sterilized and surfaces disinfected using EPA-approved products to eliminate pathogens and maintain a safe environment.

00:00:14.038 --> 00:00:16.750
Disposal of Biohazardous Materials:

00:00:16.750 --> 00:00:24.490
Use designated biohazard containers for any materials that pose a biological hazard, ensuring compliance with health regulations.

00:00:24.490 --> 00:00:27.651
Compliance with OSHA and CDC Guidelines:

00:00:27.651 --> 00:00:34.670
Follow OSHA and CDC guidelines for infection control, including staff training and regular procedure reviews.

00:00:34.670 --> 00:00:37.773
Personal Protective Equipment (PPE):

00:00:37.773 --> 00:00:41.253
Use of Gloves, Masks, and Eye Protection:

00:00:41.253 --> 00:00:48.817
Always wear gloves when handling hazardous materials, and use masks and eye protection to guard against splashes and airborne transmission.

00:00:48.817 --> 00:00:51.055
Preventing Cross-Contamination:

00:00:51.055 --> 00:00:56.096
Proper use and disposal of PPE are essential to reduce cross-contamination risks.

00:00:56.096 --> 00:01:00.621
Conduct regular training and assessments to ensure compliance with safety standards.
